cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation and its application in deep learning. The use of entropic regularization optimal transport theory and the Total Variation (TV) regularizer also suggests that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The development of a dual algorithm for the model indicates that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of measures preserving constraints in the optimal transport problem suggests that it could belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Finally, the integration of volume preserving and TV regularizer into a regularized optimal transport model could also suggest that it belongs to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
